<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
109. 
<taxonomicName authority="J.R. Grande &amp; W. Meier" authorityName="J. R. Grande &amp; W. Meier" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="yaracuyensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea yaracuyensis</emphasis>
J.R. Grande &amp; W. Meier
</taxonomicName>
, Brittonia, 63(3): 365. 2011. (Grande et al. 2011: 365)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
VENEZUELA. Yaracuy: Sierra de Aroa, 1480 m, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">L. Aristeguieta &amp; E. Foldats</emphasis>
1500 (holotype VEN34023).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Twining liana of unknown height; stem thin, cream-coloured, glabrescent. Leaves petiolarte, 7-13 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5.3-10 cm, ovate-deltoid, apex acuminate, base cordate with rounded auricles, margin often with a distinct angle, adaxially nearly glabrous, abaxially puberulent on the veins, venation prominent; petioles 4.5-7 cm, thinly puberulent. Inflorescence of 1-4-flowered pedunculate, axillary cymes; peduncles 1-4(-8) cm, puberulent; bracteoles 4-8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1 mm, linear, deciduous; secondary peduncles c. 10-15 mm; pedicels 10-25 mm; sepals subequal, obovate, mucronate, adpressed puberulous near base, outer 23-31 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
12 mm, inner sepals slightly smaller; corolla c. 7 cm long, creamy-yellow with purplish tube, funnel-shaped, thinly pubescent; limb c. 5-6 cm diam. Capsules 2-2.5 cm, subglobose, rostrate, the persistent style base c. 2 mm long; seeds 10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5 mm, tomentose and with long silky marginal hairs up to 14 mm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
